Steps to Run the Python Script
=================================
1. Install Required Python Library
On your local machine, install paramiko if you havenâ€™t already:

pip install paramiko
2. Save the Script
Copy the script into a file, e.g., install_mongo.py.

3. Run the Script
Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the directory where install_mongo.py is saved. Then run:

python install_mongo.py
4. Enter SSH Details
When prompted, enter:

Server IP (e.g., 192.168.1.100)
SSH Username (e.g., ubuntu or root)
SSH Password

The script will connect to the server and perform the MongoDB installation.

5. Verify Installation
After the script completes, you can manually check MongoDB status on the remote server:

systemctl status mongod
mongosh -u superAdmin -p
